The paper discusses color coding-related techniques for designing fast parameterized algorithms, which are typically studied in the subfield of parameterized complexity (cs.DS). The techniques mentioned in the abstract, such as narrow sieves and divide-and-color, are commonly used in the design of algorithms for problems in computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also mentions applications to problems in graph theory (cs.DM, cs.CG) and combinatorial optimization (cs.GT).
